	abstract = {Agricultural input enterprises serve as a vital element of agricultural modernization in advancing agricultural productivity, in the country's economic progress. Nevertheless, intensifying market rivalry and evolving industry conditions, agricultural input companies are encountering a growing number of obstacles and constraints, particularly in the areas of cost management and financial risk mitigation. This study aimed to improve agricultural input enterprises' management efficiency and competitiveness by exploring a cost analysis and financial warning method based on graph neural networks. We analyzed the importance of cost analysis for these enterprises and used graph neural networks to optimize cost problems by integrating Bayesian graph neural networks. This directly affected the profitability and competitive advantage of the enterprises. By conducting in-depth research on different cost factors and their impact on the economic performance of enterprises, a comprehensive understanding of the cost structure was provided. The article tried to improve existing financial early warning methods for agricultural input enterprises based on graph neural networks, utilizing the rich financial data and relationship information of graph neural networks to effectively identify financial risk factors and provide corresponding early warning models. The results of this study provided useful reference and inspiration for managers and decision-makers, promoting the sustainable development of agricultural input enterprises.},
